            "text": "Yes. The party realignment was gradual, spanning from 1948 through the 1980s. It began with Thurmond's Dixiecrat campaign in 1948, accelerated when Goldwater opposed the Civil Rights Act in 1964, was exploited by Nixon's Southern Strategy in 1968, and solidified under Reagan in 1980. In 2005, RNC Chairman Ken Mehlman formally apologized for the Southern Strategy."
