            "text": "Confederate forces fired the first shots at Fort Sumter at 4:30 AM on April 12, 1861. The Union garrison had not fired a shot. The Confederate states seceded and attacked federal property to preserve slavery, as explicitly stated in their own secession declarations."
          }
        },
